</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukelanthor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelanthor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/8/02 9:12:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3342.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My 5</span><hr size=1> Not actually a top 5 as such, I like all these about equally and think that they were (are) some of the best around in their time!<br>
<br>
1. The Bard's Tale (1985 - ish?)<br>
Great C64 adventure - not much in the way of graphics and sound, but superb for its time<br>
<br>
2. Ultima Underworld (1992?)<br>
True free-form first person dungeon adventuring arrived! Good story, decent graphics for the time and compelling gameplay.<br>
<br>
3. System Shock 2 (2000)<br>
Superb development from the original System Shock game. Moody 3d graphics, good opponent AI, eerily scary music and a bundle of choices on how to develop your character.<br>
<br>
4. Thief (1998?)<br>
Fine antidote to the first person disease of 'run-through-the-level-killing-everything-as-fast-as-you-can' syndrome! Sneak around, use your blackjack, hide the bodies, douse the torches to give you shadows to hide in. Great game, varying strategies worked to get past the same problem<br>
<br>
5. X-COM<br>
Great tactical combat in varying terrain with invading aliens. Resource management as you build your bases and train your soldiers. RP element as they go out, survive (hopefully!) and return to increase their skills. A great game with a lot of tension within its turn-based format.<br>
<br>
Honourable mentions go to Planescape, Laser Squad, Steel Panthers and the Atomic V for Victory wargames series in SVGA that brought boardgaming off the kitchen table and on to the monitor!  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ugotmayhem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gotmayhem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 382<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/8/02 9:18:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3342.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My 5</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> hide 'n go seek<br>
