<i>Is this a modrod in my pocket, or am I just happy to see you?</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/utropicsdelight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TropicsDelight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1001<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/8/02 12:53:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3342.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Top 5 games of all time</span><hr size=1> Gah, I was gonna stop posting at &quot;I live here&quot; and was gonna make the last post a going away from VCC one, this topic is too juicy though.<br>
<br>
1) Secret of Monkey Island: This game just owned, I got addicted to it, it stands as the best game of its kind ever. I played future versions, they were good but the original is the best by far.<br>
<br>
2) Privateer: I played this game for probably 300 hours before I even found out it had a storyline. Then I got stuck for another 300 hours playing it at that level. So many failed runs at capital ships..... This game owned for those that wanted a space universe where you could be a pirate, military, or merchant vessel and your faction would change and make ya cool with the right factions. The space combat was well done, and the price differences in goods at different areas was well done. The game had some problems such as the grand total of 3 ships to choose from to buy (although they could be modified with equipment and weapons) and the glaringly similar battles every time you came to a new world (always 3 ships, the same 3 ships). But nothing beats shooting people out of the sky and then tracking their escape pods with your sensors, pulling em into your hold with your tractor beam, and selling em off to slavery.<br>
<br>
3) X-Com UFO Defense: Yep, this game is that good that almost anyone who played it will put it on their list. Reasons are pretty much all stated above. One more I might add is this game scared the shit outa me. When you are moving your soldiers through the city turning corners that might get you shot dead or worse yet they might get captured and morphed into an alien themselves. Add that thrill to the best strategy game ever. Noone ever was able to match this game, it is on my hardrive right to this day.<br>
<br>
4) Final Fantasy 7: I played afew of these from the nintendo era up to number 7 with sepiroth. This one I feel had the best storyline and was unreally playable. I put days into this game, only thing I could not stand was the bloody chocobo breeding and trying to get the uber chocobo, that sucked even with a cheat off the net.<br>
<br>
5) River City Ransom: Yep old school game here, off nintendo. This game just owned, you are basically a kid from high school and the neiborhood thugs have your girlfriend held for ransom in the school. Walk the streets, meet people, buy odd foods with different properties like sushi, buy books that teach ya martial arts, become in time a veritable asskicker, then play for the next 100 hours trying to find out HOW TO GET INTO THE GOD DAMN SCHOOL! Despite that little snag I never was able to figure out this game was the best nintendo game I ever played and still makes me consider going out to buy one to play this game sometimes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukerai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kerai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Necrobish</span><br>  Posts: 3175<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/8/02 1:01:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3342.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.sowned.com/bleh/kerai2.gif height=85 width=66></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Top 5 games of all time</span><hr size=1> heh, my roomate just brought back a oldschool NES from home =P<br>
